</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,312,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
HEAD (including eyes). Much narrower than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[846,943,312,338]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[222,1372,284,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[215,1372,265,1887]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 8. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843), Myanmar, Nat Ma Taung, RBINS, adult male. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Ventral view. D. Face. E. Left lateral view. F. Head and thorax, left lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by J. Constant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071731/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Figs 8B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[955,994,312,338]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[196,1399,443,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-16@16.[189,1399,438,1884]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843) holotype, adult female. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Labels. D, F. Face. E. Ventral view. G. Right lateral view. H. Head and thorax, right lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by K. Child." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071733/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">9B</figureCitation>
). Vertex slightly produced in front of eyes, vertex about 2 times as broad as an eye, medially with reflexed protuberance (
<figureCitation box="[1250,1385,349,375]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[196,1399,443,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-16@16.[189,1399,438,1884]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843) holotype, adult female. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Labels. D, F. Face. E. Ventral view. G. Right lateral view. H. Head and thorax, right lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by K. Child." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071733/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 9B, H</figureCitation>
). Pronotum almost twice as broad as vertex, with deeply impressed point at each side of median carina, each lateral area with one rounded dark spot behind eyes, lateral carinae sinuate. Mesonotum tricarinate in disc, median carina straight, intermediate carinae curved, reaching posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1333,458,484]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[222,1372,284,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[215,1372,265,1887]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 8. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843), Myanmar, Nat Ma Taung, RBINS, adult male. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Ventral view. D. Face. E. Left lateral view. F. Head and thorax, left lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by J. Constant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071731/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Figs 8B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1347,1385,458,484]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[196,1399,443,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-16@16.[189,1399,438,1884]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843) holotype, adult female. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Labels. D, F. Face. E. Ventral view. G. Right lateral view. H. Head and thorax, right lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by K. Child." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071733/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">9B</figureCitation>
). Frons distinctly narrower from fronto-clypeal suture to apex, lateral margins carinate, medially with 2 or 3 longitudinal carinae; clypeus narrower and shorter than frons, labium elongate, median carina on clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[334,431,568,594]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[254,1338,310,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[249,1338,265,1886]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Limois kikuchii Kato, 1932, Manchuria, K. Kikuchi leg., RBINS, adult male. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Face. D. Ventral view. E. Head and thorax, right lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). F. Right lateral view. G. Labels. Photographs by J. Constant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071723" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071723/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Figs 4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[445,484,568,594]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[196,1399,443,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-16@16.[189,1399,438,1884]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843) holotype, adult female. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Labels. D, F. Face. E. Ventral view. G. Right lateral view. H. Head and thorax, right lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by K. Child." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071733/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">9D</figureCitation>
). Tegmina elongate, slightly broadened distad with the maximum width near apex, apically obliquely rounded, venation reticulate, tegmina hyperpterous, much longer than hindwing (
<figureCitation box="[198,294,641,667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[196,1399,443,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-16@16.[189,1399,438,1884]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843) holotype, adult female. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Labels. D, F. Face. E. Ventral view. G. Right lateral view. H. Head and thorax, right lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by K. Child." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071733/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Hindwing posterior margin indented at PCu level, apical cell and clavus venation reticulate (
<figureCitation box="[198,292,677,703]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[222,1372,284,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[215,1372,265,1887]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 8. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843), Myanmar, Nat Ma Taung, RBINS, adult male. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Ventral view. D. Face. E. Left lateral view. F. Head and thorax, left lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by J. Constant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071731/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Metatibiae with 4–7 lateral spines (
<figureCitation box="[726,818,677,703]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[196,1399,443,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-16@16.[189,1399,438,1884]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843) holotype, adult female. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and thorax, dorsal view. C. Labels. D, F. Face. E. Ventral view. G. Right lateral view. H. Head and thorax, right lateral view (showing reflexed protuberance of the vertex). Photographs by K. Child." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071733/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,744,1062]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
MALE GENITALIA. Pygofer symmetrical, narrow and subquadrangular in lateral view, ventrally longer than dorsally, ventrocaudal angle slightly produced caudad (
<figureCitation box="[935,1050,780,806]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[189,1389,670,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-100@17.[189,1399,637,1887]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 10. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843), Myanmar, Nat Ma Taung, RBINS, male genitalia. A. Left lateral view (except phallic complex). B. Gonostylus, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D–F. Aedeagus. D. Dorsal view. E. Ventral view. F. Left lateral view. Photographs by J. Constant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071735/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Anal tube subtriangular in lateral view, in dorsal view gradually broadened distad, apical margin concave; epiproct and paraproct separated in lateral view, in dorsal view epiproct short and broad, paraproct slender, surpassing the end of anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[350,498,890,916]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[189,1389,670,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-100@17.[189,1399,637,1887]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 10. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843), Myanmar, Nat Ma Taung, RBINS, male genitalia. A. Left lateral view (except phallic complex). B. Gonostylus, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D–F. Aedeagus. D. Dorsal view. E. Ventral view. F. Left lateral view. Photographs by J. Constant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071735/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 10A, C</figureCitation>
). Gonostyli subtriangular or oval in lateral view, submedially with a hookshaped process near dorsal side, in ventral view the styles connect only at base (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1263,926,953]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[189,1389,670,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-100@17.[189,1399,637,1887]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 10. Limois westwoodii (Hope, 1843), Myanmar, Nat Ma Taung, RBINS, male genitalia. A. Left lateral view (except phallic complex). B. Gonostylus, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D–F. Aedeagus. D. Dorsal view. E. Ventral view. F. Left lateral view. Photographs by J. Constant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4071735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4071735/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 10A, B</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus reduced, membranous endosoma with a dorsal pair of lobes surrounding a ventral pair of lobes and the sclerotized endosomal processes, the endosomal processes paired, apical portion exposed and curved dorsad in lateral view, terminally inflated (
